The calice_userlib package is the main CALICE software package.
It is used by the lcioconverter job and Marlin processors
running on the converted files.
It contains in addition data type definitions of 
calice conditions data.

It depends on ILC software packages and on the calice_cmake package,
which contains a few CALICE specific cmake macros.

For installing and compiling this package,
please follow these instructions:

https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CALICE/HowToInstallAndCompileCALICEPackages

In particular, please pay attention to the fact that you need to have the
calice_cmake package installed, and that you need to add it in the CMAKE_MODULE_PATH:

